Questions:
Which of the following procedures is considered experimental in the context of the medical experiment described in the consent form?
A) Standard chemotherapy for metastatic spine tumors;
B) Use of a carbon transpedicular stabilization system in surgical treatment combined with planning for stereotactic radiotherapy;
C) Routine post-operative care following spine surgery;
D) Administration of standard pain medication for post-surgical discomfort.

Correct answer: B) Use of a carbon transpedicular stabilization system in surgical treatment combined with planning for stereotactic radiotherapy.

What alternative treatments are available if you choose not to participate in the medical experiment for the surgical treatment of metastatic spine tumors?
A) Standard chemotherapy without the use of a carbon transpedicular stabilization system; 
B) Immediate enrollment in a different experimental study focusing on radiation therapy alone;
C) Use of a different stabilization system currently available in standard medical practice;
D) No alternatives are mentioned in the consent form.

Correct answer: D
